  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Luci di Muntagna was one of the first hotels built in Porto Cervo. The whitewashed structure was designed by architect Michele Busiri Vici and watches over the yacht club of Porto Cervo, in the heart of the stylish <a data-udi="umb://document/d3596b90f23e46bba95688a160933be3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d3596b90f23e46bba95688a160933be3}" title="Costa Smeralda Area">Costa Smeralda</a>. The typically Mediterranean building with influences from morroco, greece, Spain and Tunisia is immersed in beautiful natural surroundings. Some of the best sights in Porto Cervo are within a ten-minute walk – from pretty Stella Marie Church to streets lined by boutiques and designer shops, amoung them are the likes of BVLGARI and Dolce Gabbana.</p>
<p>Location aside, the Hotel Luci di Muntagna offers an impressive range of restaurants. Pizzeria Lucina cooks authentic Italian pizzas in its wood-fired oven. And the Kabuga Restaurant serves traditional Sardinian dishes and homemade cakes and pastries. Meanwhile, the grill barbecues lobster by the pool.</p>
<p>In the evening head to the lounge bar for a cocktail with sunset views.</p>
<p>Car hire is recommended for this hotel. Hotel Luci di Muntagna is approx. 35 mins from Olbia airport.</p>]]></description>
